 MONTAGUE1

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

Montreux, Switzerland

September 9, 1970

Dear Miss Montague,

I do not wish to appear choosy, but the new cover design won't do.2 The banal pop-arty combination of a broken chessboard inserted between Siamese twins (identical except for the forlock on one brow) is meaningless and repulsive. I do not insist on cover designs illustrating a novel realistically, but I do object to a pseudo-realism unconnected with anything in the book. It is 